Text.SourceString: I can't believe we're married, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Yesterday was magical, and I’m looking forward to many more days like that with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't believe we're married, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Yesterday was magical, and I’m looking forward to many more days like that with you.

Text.SourceString: The decor was utterly flawless! And as for the weather, oh, everything was impeccable.
Text.LocalizedString: The decor was utterly flawless! And as for the weather, oh, everything was impeccable.

Text.SourceString: You always seem to enjoy my cooking, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Here’s something else for you to try. Made with love.
Text.LocalizedString: You always seem to enjoy my cooking, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Here’s something else for you to try. Made with love.

Text.SourceString: I've made you a little something, baby!
Text.LocalizedString: I've made you a little something, baby!

Text.SourceString: Living on a farm has really changed my life.//Being close to nature and following the simple flow of the land has given me a happiness I never thought possible.
Text.LocalizedString: Living on a farm has really changed my life.//Being close to nature and following the simple flow of the land has given me a happiness I never thought possible.

Text.SourceString: I love every bit of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I love every bit of it.

Text.SourceString: Moving out of the house I grew up in... It was tough, but it also felt like the start of something new, like I was finally able to make a space that was truly mine.
Text.LocalizedString: Moving out of the house I grew up in... It was tough, but it also felt like the start of something new, like I was finally able to make a space that was truly mine.

Text.SourceString: Having all this fresh food right from the farm has got me eating healthier.//I blame you for it, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: Having all this fresh food right from the farm has got me eating healthier.//I blame you for it, baby.

Text.SourceString: Farm-to-table meals have become a daily treat that makes me feel good inside and out.
Text.LocalizedString: Farm-to-table meals have become a daily treat that makes me feel good inside and out.

Text.SourceString: Morning time on the farm is just amazing.//The sound of birds singing and the rustling of the leaves is the best way to kick off the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Morning time on the farm is just amazing.//The sound of birds singing and the rustling of the leaves is the best way to kick off the day.

Text.SourceString: I love waking up next to you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love waking up next to you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: I love sleeping next to you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love sleeping next to you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Being near the forest is nice. But I do miss the beach, it's quite a ways away from here.
Text.LocalizedString: Being near the forest is nice. But I do miss the beach, it's quite a ways away from here.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, it's a bit of a hike to get to the yoga class, but I don't mind.//<portrait=happy>I see it as a chance to connect and be mindful.//Every step gets me closer to helping my students find peace.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, it's a bit of a hike to get to the yoga class, but I don't mind.//<portrait=happy>I see it as a chance to connect and be mindful.//Every step gets me closer to helping my students find peace.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! Ready for some farming today?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! Ready for some farming today?

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking of checking in on dad. See how he's holding up.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking of checking in on dad. See how he's holding up.

Text.SourceString: We've got to grab some stuff from Sam's. I'll try to stop by later.//While I'm at it, I might grab some bread and milk for Dad and <NpcName>Ling</>.
Text.LocalizedString: We've got to grab some stuff from Sam's. I'll try to stop by later.//While I'm at it, I might grab some bread and milk for Dad and <NpcName>Ling</>.

Text.SourceString: Anything you need, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Anything you need, babe?

Text.SourceString: I haven't seen Peanut and Butter around our farm.//This path might be too far for them.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven't seen Peanut and Butter around our farm.//This path might be too far for them.

Text.SourceString: I enjoy spending time here... I can really appreciate the view of our farm.//<portrait=angry>You've done wonders to this place, babe.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy spending time here... I can really appreciate the view of our farm.//<portrait=angry>You've done wonders to this place, babe.

Text.SourceString: I thought about doing yoga out here, but maybe I'll just hang out and relax instead.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought about doing yoga out here, but maybe I'll just hang out and relax instead.

Text.SourceString: It's so peaceful here.//I'm totally in love with it.
Text.LocalizedString: It's so peaceful here.//I'm totally in love with it.

Text.SourceString: The weather is amazing today.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is amazing today.

Text.SourceString: I really care about <NpcName>Ling</> and Dad, I do.//<portrait=happy>But having a little space sometimes feels good. Not too much, just a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I really care about <NpcName>Ling</> and Dad, I do.//<portrait=happy>But having a little space sometimes feels good. Not too much, just a bit.

Text.SourceString: I really care about <NpcName>Ling</> and Dad, I do.//<portrait=happy>But having a little space sometimes feels good. Not too much, just a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I really care about <NpcName>Ling</> and Dad, I do.//<portrait=happy>But having a little space sometimes feels good. Not too much, just a bit.

Text.SourceString: I should head over to Dad's and cook dinner.//I miss those meals with <NpcName>Ling</>  and him.
Text.LocalizedString: I should head over to Dad's and cook dinner.//I miss those meals with <NpcName>Ling</>  and him.

Text.SourceString: If you're not too busy, could you come along with me?
Text.LocalizedString: If you're not too busy, could you come along with me?

Text.SourceString: Now that I'm married, I'm happy Dad found <NpcName>Ling</>.//<portrait=angry>Having someone special by your side...it's not the same as having a parent or something like that. A partner's different.//<portrait=happy>I totally get that now.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I'm married, I'm happy Dad found <NpcName>Ling</>.//<portrait=angry>Having someone special by your side...it's not the same as having a parent or something like that. A partner's different.//<portrait=happy>I totally get that now.

Text.SourceString: I'm glad Dad's got <NpcName>Ling</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad Dad's got <NpcName>Ling</>.

Text.SourceString: It's snowing out there, let's stay in and get cozy, what do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: It's snowing out there, let's stay in and get cozy, what do you think?

Text.SourceString: It's pouring outside, how about we stay in and snuggle up?
Text.LocalizedString: It's pouring outside, how about we stay in and snuggle up?

Text.SourceString: Don't go babe...please?
Text.LocalizedString: Don't go babe...please?

Text.SourceString: How's your day been, baby?
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day been, baby?

Text.SourceString: You've got a real eye for fashion, baby. Your style always turns heads.
Text.LocalizedString: You've got a real eye for fashion, baby. Your style always turns heads.

Text.SourceString: Summer at the beach, now that's something I miss.//Sunbathing, salty air... I can almost feel it.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer at the beach, now that's something I miss.//Sunbathing, salty air... I can almost feel it.

Text.SourceString: Please don't take me fishing, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=concerned>I love spending time with you, I do...it's just fishing isn't really my thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Please don't take me fishing, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=concerned>I love spending time with you, I do...it's just fishing isn't really my thing.

Text.SourceString: I get the appeal, but it's just not for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I get the appeal, but it's just not for me.

Text.SourceString: Gardening is okay. Not my top choice for a hobby, but it has its moments.//Especially when the flowers bloom, that's pretty fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Gardening is okay. Not my top choice for a hobby, but it has its moments.//Especially when the flowers bloom, that's pretty fun.

Text.SourceString: It's kinda nice, actually. Getting my hands dirty, feeling the earth, watching things grow.//<portrait=normal>I can see why you really enjoy it. Plus, the fresh veggies? Can't beat that!
Text.LocalizedString: It's kinda nice, actually. Getting my hands dirty, feeling the earth, watching things grow.//<portrait=normal>I can see why you really enjoy it. Plus, the fresh veggies? Can't beat that!

Text.SourceString: I think I got the teaching gene from my dad. But for me, it's all about yoga.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I got the teaching gene from my dad. But for me, it's all about yoga.

Text.SourceString: I love helping people find balance and peace.//I enjoy being like Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: I love helping people find balance and peace.//I enjoy being like Dad.

Text.SourceString: Living right next to a lake wasn't that glamorous, honestly.//It could get really loud.
Text.LocalizedString: Living right next to a lake wasn't that glamorous, honestly.//It could get really loud.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and <Italic>lively</>, I guess, if you want to look at it that way.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and <Italic>lively</>, I guess, if you want to look at it that way.

Text.SourceString: Every time I run out of makeup, I have to order it from Pokyo. So inconvenient.//<portrait=angry>Ugh. Living here is so complicated.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I run out of makeup, I have to order it from Pokyo. So inconvenient.//<portrait=angry>Ugh. Living here is so complicated.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how much longer I can survive living like this.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how much longer I can survive living like this.

Text.SourceString: I’m leading a yoga class at the community center tomorrow at 10 am.//When do you think I should set off, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m leading a yoga class at the community center tomorrow at 10 am.//When do you think I should set off, babe?

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to film on the beach. Always so windy, and the ground is uneven. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to film on the beach. Always so windy, and the ground is uneven. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I try to spice up yoga class by incorporating meditation sometimes.//It gets boring otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to spice up yoga class by incorporating meditation sometimes.//It gets boring otherwise.

Text.SourceString: Yes? What’s up?
Text.LocalizedString: Yes? What’s up?

Text.SourceString: I learned the right accessory can make or break an outfit.//It’s tricky, because you definitely don’t want to look tacky, like you’re trying too hard.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned the right accessory can make or break an outfit.//It’s tricky, because you definitely don’t want to look tacky, like you’re trying too hard.

Text.SourceString: You seem to, umm, be doing just fine with that.
Text.LocalizedString: You seem to, umm, be doing just fine with that.

Text.SourceString: I hate the smell of coffee. It’s so… I can’t find the right word.//Earthy? Bitter? Musty? Anyway…
Text.LocalizedString: I hate the smell of coffee. It’s so… I can’t find the right word.//Earthy? Bitter? Musty? Anyway…

Text.SourceString: Dad loves coffee, though. That’s how he starts every day, with a big cup of hot coffee.//What about you? Are you the same?
Text.LocalizedString: Dad loves coffee, though. That’s how he starts every day, with a big cup of hot coffee.//What about you? Are you the same?

Text.SourceString: I think I’m going to take it easy now.//<portrait=concerned>It’s been a hectic day, and it’s only Monday.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’m going to take it easy now.//<portrait=concerned>It’s been a hectic day, and it’s only Monday.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> has a giant display case of creepy dolls in the living room. Super weird. Not a great way to greet company, is it?//If she just kept them in the privacy of her room, it might be okay.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> has a giant display case of creepy dolls in the living room. Super weird. Not a great way to greet company, is it?//If she just kept them in the privacy of her room, it might be okay.

Text.SourceString: Whatever floats her boat, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: Whatever floats her boat, I guess.

Text.SourceString: For my carefree, effortless look, I’m wearing light foundation and a touch of lip gloss today.//<portrait=happy>You like?
Text.LocalizedString: For my carefree, effortless look, I’m wearing light foundation and a touch of lip gloss today.//<portrait=happy>You like?

Text.SourceString: You can’t get anything good around here.//Not even a decent yoga mat.
Text.LocalizedString: You can’t get anything good around here.//Not even a decent yoga mat.

Text.SourceString: Preposterous, right? I know I sound dramatic, but you know it’s true.
Text.LocalizedString: Preposterous, right? I know I sound dramatic, but you know it’s true.

Text.SourceString: Bananas are good for you, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Bananas are good for you, right?

Text.SourceString: Let’s see, what’s a good Spring look? Something flowy, definitely. A nice pastel makeup tone. What else, what else?//<portrait=angry>Are you eavesdropping on me? Of course. You would.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s see, what’s a good Spring look? Something flowy, definitely. A nice pastel makeup tone. What else, what else?//<portrait=angry>Are you eavesdropping on me? Of course. You would.

Text.SourceString: Is this…is this your Spring look? How…country.
Text.LocalizedString: Is this…is this your Spring look? How…country.

Text.SourceString: With Fall fashion, it’s all about the layers, <PlayerName>$player</>. A jacket, a scarf, whatever you want. Oh, maybe not whatever <Italic>you</> want, if you know what I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: With Fall fashion, it’s all about the layers, <PlayerName>$player</>. A jacket, a scarf, whatever you want. Oh, maybe not whatever <Italic>you</> want, if you know what I mean.

Text.SourceString: I need to prepare for the Spooky Day Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to prepare for the Spooky Day Festival.

Text.SourceString: Personally, I don’t care about the competition between Starlet and Beluga at the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=normal>But my audience eats it right up.
Text.LocalizedString: Personally, I don’t care about the competition between Starlet and Beluga at the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=normal>But my audience eats it right up.

Text.SourceString: Dad used to make me do the pumpkin-smashing game when I was a kid. Ugh!//<portrait=happy>I won a couple of times.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad used to make me do the pumpkin-smashing game when I was a kid. Ugh!//<portrait=happy>I won a couple of times.

Text.SourceString: That dusting of snow looks kinda cute on you.
Text.LocalizedString: That dusting of snow looks kinda cute on you.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> is a bit of an oddball, yeah. But she’s actually okay.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> is a bit of an oddball, yeah. But she’s actually okay.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, it’s not bad to be an oddball. The world needs more of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, it’s not bad to be an oddball. The world needs more of them.

Text.SourceString: Ugh. Spring feels so long this year. I’m so ready for Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh. Spring feels so long this year. I’m so ready for Summer.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna get the perfect Summer glow this year. I just know it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna get the perfect Summer glow this year. I just know it.

Text.SourceString: The whole island is gathering at the beach tomorrow to pick up trash.
Text.LocalizedString: The whole island is gathering at the beach tomorrow to pick up trash.

Text.SourceString: Yes. Trash.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes. Trash.

Text.SourceString: I honestly think Fall is the best time to go to the beach.//It’s way less crowded.
Text.LocalizedString: I honestly think Fall is the best time to go to the beach.//It’s way less crowded.

Text.SourceString: And the weather isn’t too hot.
Text.LocalizedString: And the weather isn’t too hot.

Text.SourceString: It’s almost the first weekend of Fall already.//All my mutuals are going to be posting pumpkin pictures soon.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s almost the first weekend of Fall already.//All my mutuals are going to be posting pumpkin pictures soon.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh! Next week will be way too late. I need to find a pumpkin before Saturday.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh! Next week will be way too late. I need to find a pumpkin before Saturday.

Text.SourceString: I spent two hours on my hair today, and the wind just blew all my hard work away.
Text.LocalizedString: I spent two hours on my hair today, and the wind just blew all my hard work away.

Text.SourceString: Ugh. So annoying.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh. So annoying.

Text.SourceString: Your boots are so thick. They look super cozy, by the way. Are they designer?
Text.LocalizedString: Your boots are so thick. They look super cozy, by the way. Are they designer?

Text.SourceString: I have to get myself a pair. So country. But I don’t know where I’d wear them.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to get myself a pair. So country. But I don’t know where I’d wear them.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t gotten anything for the twins.//Their birthday’s coming up.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t gotten anything for the twins.//Their birthday’s coming up.

Text.SourceString: I forgot to get gifts for the twins. Maybe I should just give them to them tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I forgot to get gifts for the twins. Maybe I should just give them to them tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: The Coral Inn twins, of course. It’s their birthday today.
Text.LocalizedString: The Coral Inn twins, of course. It’s their birthday today.

Text.SourceString: I really shouldn’t be out in the rain too long.
Text.LocalizedString: I really shouldn’t be out in the rain too long.

Text.SourceString: Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!
Text.LocalizedString: Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait until it stops. I’m just not a sit-around-doing-nothing kind of girl, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait until it stops. I’m just not a sit-around-doing-nothing kind of girl, you know.

Text.SourceString: I really shouldn’t be out in the rain too long.
Text.LocalizedString: I really shouldn’t be out in the rain too long.

Text.SourceString: It’s the perfect weather for self-reflective meditation.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the perfect weather for self-reflective meditation.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever been afraid your house might be destroyed by a storm?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever been afraid your house might be destroyed by a storm?

Text.SourceString: I forgot my umbrella. Argh.
Text.LocalizedString: I forgot my umbrella. Argh.

Text.SourceString: I hope it stops storming tomorrow. It’s so boring to stay inside all day.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it stops storming tomorrow. It’s so boring to stay inside all day.

Text.SourceString: Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!
Text.LocalizedString: Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Leah</> is ignoring you.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Leah</> is ignoring you.]

Text.SourceString: Keep your body moving in Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>. It helps you stay warm.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep your body moving in Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>. It helps you stay warm.

Text.SourceString: I could use some sun right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use some sun right about now.

Text.SourceString: I can’t walk in all this snow.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t walk in all this snow.

Text.SourceString: The snow is going to ruin my shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is going to ruin my shoes.

Text.SourceString: Do I look okay today?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I look okay today?

Text.SourceString: Remember to moisturize after washing your hands. You don’t want to get all chapped.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to moisturize after washing your hands. You don’t want to get all chapped.

Text.SourceString: Being back here brings back so many memories. It's nice to visit.
Text.LocalizedString: Being back here brings back so many memories. It's nice to visit.

Text.SourceString: Even though I'm married now, there's still something comforting about this place.//It's like stepping back into my childhood.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I'm married now, there's still something comforting about this place.//It's like stepping back into my childhood.

Text.SourceString: This place stays the same. It's like I never left.
Text.LocalizedString: This place stays the same. It's like I never left.

Text.SourceString: This one time, I made a video in the forest, and when I reviewed the footage, I saw I’d caught a slithering shadow.
Text.LocalizedString: This one time, I made a video in the forest, and when I reviewed the footage, I saw I’d caught a slithering shadow.

Text.SourceString: I thought it was a monster at first, but it turned out to be Taco. What a relief!
Text.LocalizedString: I thought it was a monster at first, but it turned out to be Taco. What a relief!

Text.SourceString: I don’t like wearing my hair down. It always seems to get in the way.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like wearing my hair down. It always seems to get in the way.

Text.SourceString: People think it must be so great living right next to a park, but to be honest, it gets very noisy on the weekends.
Text.LocalizedString: People think it must be so great living right next to a park, but to be honest, it gets very noisy on the weekends.

Text.SourceString: You need to join my yoga class sometime.//<portrait=happy>It’ll be fun!
Text.LocalizedString: You need to join my yoga class sometime.//<portrait=happy>It’ll be fun!

Text.SourceString: We need to spice things up a bit around here. It looks so dull and one-dimensional.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to spice things up a bit around here. It looks so dull and one-dimensional.

Text.SourceString: I’m posting my health checkup video as soon as I get home.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m posting my health checkup video as soon as I get home.

Text.SourceString: You look a bit under the weather.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe cut back a little on the farming.
Text.LocalizedString: You look a bit under the weather.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe cut back a little on the farming.

Text.SourceString: Having a farm doesn’t seem so bad, now that I think about it.//You get to play with cute animals every day.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a farm doesn’t seem so bad, now that I think about it.//You get to play with cute animals every day.

Text.SourceString: Happy Friday!//I have my yoga lesson down for tomorrow. I’m ready!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Friday!//I have my yoga lesson down for tomorrow. I’m ready!

Text.SourceString: I’m going to stretch a little today. Not too much.//Get in the flow, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to stretch a little today. Not too much.//Get in the flow, you know?

Text.SourceString: I made some stew last night from a recipe I got from the internet.//It was horrible! Too many peas, for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I made some stew last night from a recipe I got from the internet.//It was horrible! Too many peas, for sure.

Text.SourceString: I still have some leftovers in the fridge, but to be honest, I’m not touching it.//<portrait=concerned>Do you want to try it?
Text.LocalizedString: I still have some leftovers in the fridge, but to be honest, I’m not touching it.//<portrait=concerned>Do you want to try it?

Text.SourceString: Cooking is a good way to unwind.//It’s a solo activity too. It doesn’t usually require assistance.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking is a good way to unwind.//It’s a solo activity too. It doesn’t usually require assistance.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a very good cook, but I can make some stuff, you know?//The first recipe I got was from Mom. Cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a very good cook, but I can make some stuff, you know?//The first recipe I got was from Mom. Cookies.

Text.SourceString: Cookies were the only thing she could make back in the day.//Maybe even now. I’m not sure.
Text.LocalizedString: Cookies were the only thing she could make back in the day.//Maybe even now. I’m not sure.

Text.SourceString: The beach here isn’t so bad.//I like the white sand.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach here isn’t so bad.//I like the white sand.

Text.SourceString: It isn’t easy to do yoga on the beach. The sand eats your feet!
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t easy to do yoga on the beach. The sand eats your feet!

Text.SourceString: Do you feel that? The wind is nice today.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you feel that? The wind is nice today.

Text.SourceString: Don’t fall asleep here.//<portrait=angry>You’ll wake up sunburned on one side of your body. Disaster!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t fall asleep here.//<portrait=angry>You’ll wake up sunburned on one side of your body. Disaster!

Text.SourceString: I used to swim with Dad right over there, behind the big rocks.//<portrait=happy>He used to make me wear this really <Italic>ugly</> hat. Ha ha ha! I hated it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to swim with Dad right over there, behind the big rocks.//<portrait=happy>He used to make me wear this really <Italic>ugly</> hat. Ha ha ha! I hated it.

Text.SourceString: I kept the hat in my closet for years. Got rid of it several years ago. I put it with the knitting <NpcName>Ling</> donates to the city every year.//<portrait=sad>Good memories.
Text.LocalizedString: I kept the hat in my closet for years. Got rid of it several years ago. I put it with the knitting <NpcName>Ling</> donates to the city every year.//<portrait=sad>Good memories.

Text.SourceString: It’s too hot for me to let my hair down. Better to keep it up.//<portrait=happy>Besides, I like it like this.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too hot for me to let my hair down. Better to keep it up.//<portrait=happy>Besides, I like it like this.

Text.SourceString: I got this outfit in San Franciskyo. You like?//<portrait=normal>It’s always so cold there. I went in Summer, and it was freezing. In fact, this is what I was wearing there in Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: I got this outfit in San Franciskyo. You like?//<portrait=normal>It’s always so cold there. I went in Summer, and it was freezing. In fact, this is what I was wearing there in Summer!

Text.SourceString: I just got my kitchen cleaned up. Oh my.//It was good hand-strengthening exercise for yoga, ’cause some of those stains are tougher than… Ugh, I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: I just got my kitchen cleaned up. Oh my.//It was good hand-strengthening exercise for yoga, ’cause some of those stains are tougher than… Ugh, I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: My hands are all sore now.
Text.LocalizedString: My hands are all sore now.

Text.SourceString: Do you think this is my color?//I like the dress, but I want to know what you think.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think this is my color?//I like the dress, but I want to know what you think.

Text.SourceString: Is it a good shade of pink?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it a good shade of pink?

Text.SourceString: Do you think this is my color?//I want to know what you think.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think this is my color?//I want to know what you think.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually wear blue, but I figured it’s Winter.//Blue seems fitting, no?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually wear blue, but I figured it’s Winter.//Blue seems fitting, no?

Text.SourceString: I could never get upset with you.//<portrait=sad>Sorry if I always seem annoyed. It’s just, you know, my face.
Text.LocalizedString: I could never get upset with you.//<portrait=sad>Sorry if I always seem annoyed. It’s just, you know, my face.

Text.SourceString: Probably not a bad idea to donate some of my out-of-season things. Make room for new stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Probably not a bad idea to donate some of my out-of-season things. Make room for new stuff.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know a lot about charity and all that.//<portrait=angry>I’ll have to ask the mayor what to do with my unwanted stuff. Or I could ask <NpcName>Ling</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know a lot about charity and all that.//<portrait=angry>I’ll have to ask the mayor what to do with my unwanted stuff. Or I could ask <NpcName>Ling</>.

Text.SourceString: I should really get my closet reorganized. There’s way too much stuff in there.
Text.LocalizedString: I should really get my closet reorganized. There’s way too much stuff in there.

Text.SourceString: You look dashing today, <PlayerName>$player</>. So effortless.
Text.LocalizedString: You look dashing today, <PlayerName>$player</>. So effortless.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should try wearing my hair down once in a while. Do you think I’d look good like that?
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should try wearing my hair down once in a while. Do you think I’d look good like that?

Text.SourceString: I get annoyed at Dad sometimes.//How could he be happy here on such a secluded island, scraping by on the bare minimum?
Text.LocalizedString: I get annoyed at Dad sometimes.//How could he be happy here on such a secluded island, scraping by on the bare minimum?

Text.SourceString: But it’s hard to stay mad at Dad for long.//He’s an inspiration, to be honest. I didn’t get it at first, but he showed me there are things more important than wealth and fame.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s hard to stay mad at Dad for long.//He’s an inspiration, to be honest. I didn’t get it at first, but he showed me there are things more important than wealth and fame.

Text.SourceString: Aww! The farmer look really suits you. With the dirt smudges and untidy hair.//<portrait=normal>I think I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww! The farmer look really suits you. With the dirt smudges and untidy hair.//<portrait=normal>I think I like it.

Text.SourceString: You saw <NPCName>Charles</> at the Tavern alone?
Text.LocalizedString: You saw <NPCName>Charles</> at the Tavern alone?

Text.SourceString: Poor thing. Say hello to him, will you?
Text.LocalizedString: Poor thing. Say hello to him, will you?

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! Didn’t see you there, baby!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey! Didn’t see you there, baby!

Text.SourceString: What do you think of my makeup? I always worry I’d look tired without it.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think of my makeup? I always worry I’d look tired without it.

Text.SourceString: Oh, look at me! Asking for advice.//I’m becoming more and more like you, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m one outfit away from being a down-to-earth farmer.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, look at me! Asking for advice.//I’m becoming more and more like you, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m one outfit away from being a down-to-earth farmer.

Text.SourceString: Growing up, I always wanted to be like Mom. You know, with the fancy dresses and exotic trips. But not anymore.//As I get older, I want to be more like Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, I always wanted to be like Mom. You know, with the fancy dresses and exotic trips. But not anymore.//As I get older, I want to be more like Dad.

Text.SourceString: He’s… Dad’s led such an honest life.//<portrait=happy>He seems happy, you know? Content. I want to feel like that more than I want to look nice.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s… Dad’s led such an honest life.//<portrait=happy>He seems happy, you know? Content. I want to feel like that more than I want to look nice.

Text.SourceString: I wish I didn’t have to say this, but it was hard being raised by my mom. She was always so glamorous and put together.//It’s a lot of pressure to be around her, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I didn’t have to say this, but it was hard being raised by my mom. She was always so glamorous and put together.//It’s a lot of pressure to be around her, you know.

Text.SourceString: If you’re a little kid, you have no choice but to look up to the closest grown-up around. In my case, it was my mom.//<portrait=normal>At the beginning, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re a little kid, you have no choice but to look up to the closest grown-up around. In my case, it was my mom.//<portrait=normal>At the beginning, anyway.

Text.SourceString: I hated my parents for leaving me behind and just carrying on with their lives.//Once they separated, Mom moved out. Off she went.
Text.LocalizedString: I hated my parents for leaving me behind and just carrying on with their lives.//Once they separated, Mom moved out. Off she went.

Text.SourceString: I used to spend Summers with either Mom or Dad. A birthday party with Mom. Or Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to spend Summers with either Mom or Dad. A birthday party with Mom. Or Dad.

Text.SourceString: Divorce was hard on a little kid. Sometimes, I still wish they’d just get along.//I see my friends’ parents do it, so why can’t they?
Text.LocalizedString: Divorce was hard on a little kid. Sometimes, I still wish they’d just get along.//I see my friends’ parents do it, so why can’t they?

Text.SourceString: I could learn a lot from Dad. He found his passion early in life and stuck with it.//Never once was he tempted to give up teaching for more money.
Text.LocalizedString: I could learn a lot from Dad. He found his passion early in life and stuck with it.//Never once was he tempted to give up teaching for more money.

Text.SourceString: I have a lot of memories with Dad.//Building sandcastles, going camping, carving pumpkins, catching fish…
Text.LocalizedString: I have a lot of memories with Dad.//Building sandcastles, going camping, carving pumpkins, catching fish…

Text.SourceString: Huh? Oh, fishing. Right, right.
Text.LocalizedString: Huh? Oh, fishing. Right, right.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t heard from Mom in over a year. I wonder how she’s doing.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t heard from Mom in over a year. I wonder how she’s doing.

Text.SourceString: She’s probably really busy. She’s a big deal, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s probably really busy. She’s a big deal, you know.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, this Sunday is the planting day, yes?//I’m not looking forward to it.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, this Sunday is the planting day, yes?//I’m not looking forward to it.

Text.SourceString: Why do we need to plant trees all day?!//We should just celebrate by having another barbecue potluck instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Why do we need to plant trees all day?!//We should just celebrate by having another barbecue potluck instead.

Text.SourceString: Are you excited about the Animal Festival? I could do without the smelly cows, but I can’t wait to see all the pets!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you excited about the Animal Festival? I could do without the smelly cows, but I can’t wait to see all the pets!

Text.SourceString: Let me give you some advice about constructing the perfect Summer look.//Use bright colors, but don’t be obnoxious about it. You can expose some skin, but make it tasteful.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me give you some advice about constructing the perfect Summer look.//Use bright colors, but don’t be obnoxious about it. You can expose some skin, but make it tasteful.

Text.SourceString: I just love Fall fashion. Such a shame it’s so hard to get things shipped to the island, though.//<portrait=concerned>Oh, I know they sell some things here. They’re just…not to my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: I just love Fall fashion. Such a shame it’s so hard to get things shipped to the island, though.//<portrait=concerned>Oh, I know they sell some things here. They’re just…not to my taste.

Text.SourceString: I look a bit out of place in this suit right now.//But that’s what fashion is sometimes. Be bold and stand out!
Text.LocalizedString: I look a bit out of place in this suit right now.//But that’s what fashion is sometimes. Be bold and stand out!

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival made me miss Mom.//She never took me to one. That’s the weird thing.//How can you miss something that never happened?
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival made me miss Mom.//She never took me to one. That’s the weird thing.//How can you miss something that never happened?

Text.SourceString: The problem with Winter is I don’t want to look like a ball of fabric, but I also don’t want to freeze.//It’s a tough balancing act.
Text.LocalizedString: The problem with Winter is I don’t want to look like a ball of fabric, but I also don’t want to freeze.//It’s a tough balancing act.

Text.SourceString: I always look forward to the snow. It makes the town more magical and interesting.
Text.LocalizedString: I always look forward to the snow. It makes the town more magical and interesting.

Text.SourceString: I like this town, actually. I know I complain a lot.//It’s the only way I know how to cope, I guess. I wanted to hate Dad and this town for keeping me here.//But let’s face it. It’s not them keeping me here. It’s Mom who didn’t want me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this town, actually. I know I complain a lot.//It’s the only way I know how to cope, I guess. I wanted to hate Dad and this town for keeping me here.//But let’s face it. It’s not them keeping me here. It’s Mom who didn’t want me.

Text.SourceString: It gives me comfort to blame the town. I know, I know. It isn’t fair. But it helps me feel better.//Is that so bad?//<portrait=happy>But the shopping <Italic>does</> suck here. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: It gives me comfort to blame the town. I know, I know. It isn’t fair. But it helps me feel better.//Is that so bad?//<portrait=happy>But the shopping <Italic>does</> suck here. Heh heh!
